The Telegraph - Calcutta
 East Bengal in Leicester, with Boca Juniors
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: East Bengal have found some more reason to look beyond the national confines. After having featured in the ASEAN Cup and AFC Cup, they have now received an invitation to a tournament to be played in England in July-August. This tournament will be organised by Leicester City. The occasion is to mark the English clubs 120th anniversary. Announcing this on Monday, East Bengal secretary Kalyan Majumdar said that apart from East Bengal and Leicester City, Boca Juniors (Argentina) and Borussia Dortmund (Germany) are the others in the fray. It was learnt that East Bengal are likely to meet the hosts in the first match  a virtual semi-final. The East Bengal official informed that starting this season, they will offer the players and the coach two-three year contracts. Normally, all are offered one-year contracts. He added that East Bengal will also build two teams so that different set of players can be fielded, keeping in mind the importance of the tournaments. Majumdar also said that the club would like to retain Subhas Bhowmick as coach.  Copyright 
